      <guid isPermaLink="false">05e56611caca36be7e442f3f751c3f94a23167c5</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 26 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Carol has been best friends with Nolan for ten years, long before he ever knew her as Carol. Until recently, her feelings towards him have been one-sided, but her transition threatens to change their dynamic permanently. The Understudy is a short story about the complex relationship dynamics that many trans-women have to deal with in real life and how they affect them, it centers around a breakup told in a descending series of flashbacks that describe the relationship of the two main characters and how their dynamics have shifted.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2143547-the-understudy/chapter/2143552/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;The Understudy&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;She gazed out the window and felt the last rays of the evening winter sun graze her skin. The faint rumbles of a nearby freight train rattled the building gently. She’s alone in her mind for a brief moment in time. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Behind her, the bed buckles and the springs creak. She twitches as she feels a cool hand trace the nape of her neck down to her shoulder. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“-rol. Carol. You ok? Hey!” The voice echoed faintly in her ears, like hearing a phone call through a thin wall, and she turned her gaze slowly to meet his. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, yeah I’m fine,” she strained, “you want another round, or was that &lt;i&gt;‘her’&lt;/i&gt; calling you?” She’s trying desperately to hide the disdain in her voice, but she’s failing miserably, and he can tell&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You don’t have to talk about her like that you know. She’s really not-”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah I get it, I get it. I’m sorry, just forget it. Go. I know you’ve been waiting to…” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He hesitated for a moment, before scooting up to the edge of the bed with her, “I can stay a bit longer.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She wanted to tell him to go. To fuck off, that it was over, and that she never wanted to see him again. But that would mean she would be alone. Well and truly alone. Anything would be better than that. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Just. Stay…” she muttered, before resting her head gently against his shoulder. He was warm. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah… yeah OK,” he said softly as he stroked her hair. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As they sat in the silence, Carol’s mind filled with memories of the past. How did she do this to herself?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;…&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;1 Year Ago&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Carol tugged uncomfortably at the skirt that currently clung to her, “Are you sure it looks alright?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Lily nodded vigorously, “You look GREAT,” and she wasn’t lying. The skirt was one of Lily’s old ones, and it was at least two sizes too small, but Carol had managed to squeeze into it somehow. Afterwards, they gave her a little bit of light makeup and a top to match it. She really did look lovely. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She gave a shy smile and turned to look back in the mirror, “Yeah… I guess I do.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;…&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;2 Years Ago&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron sat in the booth quietly. It had been a little over two years since he’d last seen Nolan. They’d been best friends since the seventh grade, but college had other plans, and their schedules never seemed to align. Nolan had gone and crashed and burned out in Montana while Cameron had made the choice to stay behind in Washington. It’d been so long. Maybe he’d finally be brave enough to tell him.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Before he could lose himself in thought, Nolan walked in. With… a girl. Cameron had no idea who this was for a brief moment, but once he did, he felt his stomach drop. This was that girl Nolan had been on and on about as of late. He was pretty sure her name was… &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey! Cameron, this is Anna!” Nolan proclaimed as he made his way over to the table. He was wearing that stupid grin that always softened Cameron’s mood, no matter how foul. Before he could react, Nolan had pulled him out of the booth into a colossal bear hug. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron tensed for a second, before inevitably melting fully into the embrace. Nolan was warm. Soft but strong, less like an athlete and more like a manual laborer. He was the only person taller than Cameron, and that was the best part. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She could have stayed like that forever.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He’d been fully prepared to, until a shrill voice pierced his ears and brought him crashing back to reality, “Oh my god! You’re Cameron! So nice to meet my boyfriend's &lt;i&gt;boyfriend&lt;/i&gt;!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron froze for a moment as he heard this, before awkwardly recovering, “Y-yeah, that’s me haha. Nice to meet you too,” he said as he tried to remember the basics of socialization. They sat down and struck a friendly conversation, but Cameron hadn’t been very chatty. He kept stealing glances at Anna, and every time he did, the sense of dread he felt in his chest only grew more and more powerful. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;‘Oh God,’ &lt;/i&gt;he thought, &lt;i&gt;‘She’s beautiful…’ &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;…&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;4 Years Ago&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I hate this, why are we going so far?” Cameron grumbled. His feet were sore, and he’d already been whacked in the face by several branches so far. They had been walking for at least forty-five minutes, and Nolan &lt;i&gt;still&lt;/i&gt; wouldn’t tell him where they were going. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’ll just-have to-wait and seeeeee,” Nolan said in a sing-songy voice. For a brief moment Cameron considered throwing something at him. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ugh, you’re an ass,” he shot back. He wanted to say something else, but was frankly too tired to complain anymore. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They’d continue to walk for another twenty minutes, but Cameron swore up and down it was a whole extra hour.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Finally, Nolan had piped up, “We’re here!” Cameron whipped his head up at the sudden announcement and finally saw where Nolan had guided them. It was a small cliff face overlooking the river. The sun was casting a fiery orange glow across the water's surface, and a cool summer breeze grazed his skin. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Here, siddown,” Nolan gestured to the rocks at the top of the cliff face. Cameron looked down and finally figured out why Nolan had wanted to come here. Not only was it beautiful, the rocks at the top of the cliff face had been worn in such a way that they were perfectly chair shaped. For a moment, Cameron thought of all the couples who must have come here before them before taking his seat next to Nolan. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ta-da!” Cameron turned his head to see what Nolan had been so proud about and saw in his hands two messy, bright green joints. “I rolled ‘em myself, what do you think?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He wanted to laugh. Really badly. But the look on Nolan’s face was just so earnest that he simply stifled it and said “Wow, yeah man that looks great.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Dick,” he chuckled. Apparently, this hadn’t been as smooth as he thought, and Nolan slugged him on the arm gently.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Here,” he said while passing the joint to Cameron, “light it will ya? I always end up choking.” Cameron took it to mouth before flicking the lighter a few times. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh mother-” Cameron cursed under his breath as he continuously flicked at the flighter. No matter how hard he tried, the wind would simply snuff the flame as soon as he lit it. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Here,” Nolan said as he inched closer and held out his hands to cover the lighter. Cameron’s heart skipped a beat as he got closer, and he had no idea why. As he leaned in to shelter the little lighter from the wind, he could smell cologne mixed faintly with sweat and the faint notes of tree sap from their walk. In that brief moment, all Cameron could think about was how badly she wanted Nolan to kiss her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;…&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;6 Years Ago&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron felt the wind fly out of him as he hit the ground. He let out an exasperated groan and grumbled, “Do we really have to play on the same football team?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Nolan pulled him to his feet, “Because you said you would! It’ll be fun, I swear.” Cameron brushed the grass off his shorts and grabbed a drink of water. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah… if you say so,” he said as he made his way over to the shade under the trees to sit down. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Nolan quickly followed suit and sat next to him quietly. He looked at Cameron and saw the pained expression on his face. Something wasn’t sitting right with him. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Be honest… do you actually want to play?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron looked shocked for a moment, then guilty, “...No, not really. It's just. Everyone here keeps telling me ‘Oh you’re so tall, why aren’t you playing football!’ and I just. I don’t know, I guess I felt like I was obligated to. It’s what we’re supposed to do. Right?” Cameron paused for a moment before sheepishly adding, “Plus, we’d get to hangout more…” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Well why did you say so!” It suddenly all made sense, Cameron had always been kind of self-conscious about his height, though Nolan never really understood why. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I just didn’t want to upset you I guess.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re not gonna upset me, I’d rather just keep hanging out like normal instead of making you miserable all the time!” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Really?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Of course! We’re best friends right?” Nolan spoke those last words with so much pride that Cameron could feel himself tearing up a little. Before he could react, Nolan’s arms wrapped around him and pulled him in for a tight, warm embrace. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And she felt her anxiety melt away. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;…&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;8 Years Ago&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron trudged along the mud covered track, picking at the ill-fitting gym uniform their middle school had forced them to wear. He hadn’t been paying attention at that point, he just wanted this to be over already. His legs ached, he was caked in mud, his lungs burned and his forehead was sticky with sweat. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He’d seen Nolan a couple times in passing, but the much more athletic boy had managed to keep a consistent pace, so Cameron only saw him when he lapped the track. He’d been content with this setup, until he ran into another boy on the track named Logan. They’d never gotten along, and today was no exception.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Heyyyy, look at Cameron! He’s all by himself today. Guess his boyfriend didn’t feel like dealing with him today.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron felt his ears go bright red and in a moment of embarrassment and impulsivity, he whipped his body around to look at him, “Fuck off Logan, he’s not my boyfriend,” he snapped. He knew he shouldn’t give him the time of day, but he was far too exhausted for rational decision making at this point. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ooo look at that, he can speak by himself. Normally his little butt buddy does it for him. Do you need us to go get him for you sweetheart?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I said leave me alone,” Cameron said as he hunkered down and picked up the pace. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey where you going! We’re just joking, that's all!” Logan laughed as they caught up with Cameron easily. He was too tired to outpace them. “Come on, quit being such a little fa-” he was interrupted by the loud crack of Cameron’s fist on his face. Immediately, Cameron knew what he had done and he went deathly pale before turning on his heel to sprint away. Before he could get away however, one of the boys standing next to Logan wrapped his arm around his neck and held Cameron in place as the other two boys took turns taking cheap shots at him. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron kicked vigorously but it was no use, the boy who had him was far stronger. It seemed like he was destined for a beating. But all of a sudden, the blows simply quit as a large silhouette plowed into Logan, knocking him to the ground. It was Nolan.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“FUCK OFF. ALL OF YOU,” he shouted at the other boys before turning his gaze to Logan, “Don’t you ever touch my friends again,” he said. As menacing as was trying to be, Cameron found it a little hard to take the sweet boy seriously. Though it seems Logan had no similar problem.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Y-yeah, sorry man…” he meekly squeaked out before running off to catch up with the other boys. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Nolan quickly turned his gaze to Cameron, “Are you OK?! What happened?” He asked frantically as he searched Cameron for obvious wounds. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah I’m fine, swear it, thanks to you.” Cameron reassured him. He knew that Nolan’s timing didn’t exactly do anything to dissuade the rumours. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But she didn’t care. She was just glad he was here.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;…&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Present Day&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You alright?” She heard Nolan ask faintly. She was back in the room. Her mind locked firmly in the present.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She looked into his eyes, searching for a feeling. She was hoping for concern, maybe even anger or annoyance at her behavior. But no. It was the same look she’d seen time and time again.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It was &lt;i&gt;pity&lt;/i&gt;. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And in that moment she knew he didn’t love her. Not like that. She would be cursed, some fragile broken thing designed to be nothing but pitied and used and discarded later, doomed to forever play the understudy to the whirlwind romance the two of them starred in. The &lt;i&gt;normal&lt;/i&gt; couple. Whenever he was bored, whenever she left town, whenever he would broach the barrier of love and affection that defined friend and &lt;i&gt;girl&lt;/i&gt;friend, she would be there. Waiting for him. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;‘Fuck that,’ &lt;/i&gt;she thought. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She couldn’t do it anymore. She was awash in a wave of disgust, anger, love and &lt;i&gt;contempt&lt;/i&gt;. Contempt for him, contempt for Anna, contempt for &lt;i&gt;herself&lt;/i&gt;. When had she become so pathetic? Better yet, when had he? What had happened to the sweet, brave, honest boy she’d been best friends with. &lt;i&gt;That she fell in love with. &lt;/i&gt;Was it her fault?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She sat there, wordlessly. Time seemingly slowed to a crawl, and the dreadful silence lingered like a cloud of invisible poison. Finally, after what felt like an eternity, she let go. She pulled her head from his shoulder and gently dropped his hand before placing a single, tender kiss on his lips before standing up, and walking out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;…&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;10 Years Ago&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron looked up and down at his schedule frantically. It was his first day of middle school in a new town, and he was terrified. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He’d been assigned a tour guide to show him around, another student named Aiden. But when lunch time had rolled around, Aiden ditched him, leaving him to figure out where the last of his classes would be. And he was starting to panic.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He’d been too afraid to ask anyone for help, not that they seemed inclined to lend it. All except one boy who seemed to notice his panic.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey, are you alright? You look a little lost.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Um, yeah, a little.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Here, show me your schedule.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cameron did as he was told and submitted his schedule for an inspection. The boy took it and started combing through. As he did, a flash realization struck him like a lightning bolt. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Wait, you’re the new kid!” It wasn’t a question so much as it was a statement and it caught Cameron off guard. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Ha ha, yeah… you got me,” Cameron chuckled awkwardly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What happened to your guide? It was supposed to be Aiden, yeah?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, I think he got bored or something. I haven’t seen him for a while.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Without another word, the other boy threw his arm around Cameron’s shoulders in an over-exaggerated fashion and started them forwards.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Well no worries, I’ll be your guide! Stick with me, I know EVERYTHING about this place,” he beamed triumphantly. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“O-oh. Really? Thanks…” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh yeah, what’s your name by the way?” The boy asked&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It’s Cameron. What’s yours”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m Nolan! It’s good to meet you!” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;i&gt;…&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
