      <title>Wildflowers of Ruin</title>
      <author> Downy_Roses </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/2116689/wildflowers-of-ruin/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2116689-wildflowers-of-ruin/chapter/2116691/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">ae4b3fd3bd76961b82f552d5eaa180da32b8c344</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 15 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Briar and Lily. Doggirl mech pilot and catgirl cyborg assassin, clones and sisters, have been separated for thirteen years since the death of their "mother" Tulip. Thirteen years of a longing neither wants to admit to.&lt;br /&gt; But now, finally at 23, they're stationed at the same city . . . a chance to reconnect in person .  . . &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Just as the world starts to go to shit. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;(Siscest cyberpunk mechsploitation with Kaiju and a mild apocalypse)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/2116689-wildflowers-of-ruin/chapter/2116691/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Ruin&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;POV: Cerberus - Briar Vix (she/it) &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I hate the taste of granola. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The dull sweetness, as the dry flakes and crumbles of grain cut at my mouth and dampen in battleworn drool . . . I wish I had any jerky left . . . but it eases the pains in my stomach all the same.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;So I pulled another bar from my jacket’s leather pocket. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;So I shove down another bite.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As with a groaning twist of overheating hydraulics, and a static pinch of the neural link in my neck, I shove another Illrhyian’s hulking fish-like head into a wall of solid concrete and spite. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Smearing a painting of dripping cerulean and cloud-pale scales, like the sky of Terra . . . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;{Like her eyes.} &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It thinks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I ignore its thoughts, pushing them to the back of our mind. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Now&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; is not the time. Even in a mech as reinforced and high tech as HECATE, I'm only running at half capacity; And the flickering red LEDs reflecting in my dull blue eyes, and beeping alarms burning my dropping ears, won't let me forget. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;We’re running out of time. More shapes, as large as my spindly chassis or larger, crawl and lumber over the remains of the outer wall and the silent urban sector around me. We’re spread too thin . . . It's only u– only me here. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And the foul scent of copper and ammonia burns just beyond my intake filters . . . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The fish faced-spawn of this mudball. . .  fucking aquatic pieces of evolutionary shi—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&amp;lt;And one of them is charging right at us. Please dodge.&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Breath growls between my fangs, crackled lip stinging, as I wrench the controls to the side. Narrowly avoiding the cracking of a sensuous tail, finely scraping the dark paint off HECATE’s side. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It stings all the same.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Leaping forward, my steel body springs with the hydraulic lurch of her insectoid legs. Dark talons sinking into soft blue flesh. Ripping and tearing as their meat scatters to pulp across the street.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I scream.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Corpses fall.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Guts and heads dance under my clawed hands. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Metal groans.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Something hits me.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Something around my coiled form snaps. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I stumble.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Its claws pierce through the plating of HECATE’s chest, wires alight with blistering pain, as my jaw tenses in shock. Sensors blaring.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As coolant and hydraulics drips onto the battlefield . . . and into the cockpit. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Soaking my once branded tanktop in black oil  . . . as it mixes with the pooling red. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;{Shit. Shit. Shit.} &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Our breath quickens as our hand traces the ivory claw.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&amp;lt;Breathe. We will be okay.&amp;gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Breathe in. Breathe out. Look out the sensors . . . heaving stuttering movements . . . slowing . . .  it's dying at least. &lt;em&gt;WE.&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span&gt;ARE NOT. OKAY. FUCK.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;[-rberus.]&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I catch over the comms. My ears flicker. She sounds . . . oddly panicked . . . usually Handlers are colder. She didn't care about thi— &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;[This is Cheshire. I’m on my way to your location. Are you alive?]&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;{Not Handler?}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Not one of the Handlers. That name . .  its familiar. But thinking . . . is hard. I can barely stumble against the wall . . . as we slide against an Illrhyian’s corpse. Half dismembered arm . . . still stuck through us. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Almost eroritc. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;[Yes . . .]&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; Is all I can sputter, as things grow dim on the edges . . . the red lights reflecting, my hungered face in the shattered glass in front of me. A mess of tangled brown hair, freckles, and a weary distance some would call "psychologically concerning”. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Cracks are pale and growing. Evening air . . . leaks in with the fettered scent of distant ash and decaying xeno. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It's &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;almost &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;satisfying. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I would laugh if that didn't hurt like fuck . . . even if I wasn't hopped up on all the stimulants and pain meds coursing through my engineered caniform flesh.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I'd been stabbed before . . . this one didn’t look good.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;{Help is coming . . . }&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; Is all the weak one said. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I don’t have the heart . . . or blood flow, to argue with it. Everything is growing dim and dull . . . I can barely hold onto the controls. At least I did a good job. The sector is safe. Good Hound . . . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I’ve made it longer than mo—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;[You promised.]&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; The words cut through, clear and cold, worry and spite mix an equal measure as the comm system fizzes out. The reactor shutting offline, lights blinking out, as the coolant drains away. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I must be dreaming . . . because beyond the dark glass panes are a silhouette. A woman. Metal softly tinking and scraping, she clambers up HECATE’s punctured side. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Metal whines. Glass shatters. As pale chrome claws glint in the amber sunset. Eyes flickering softly, every shade of the falling rain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And a smile, sharp and thin.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Hungry and pained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;{Danger}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I try to move.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Twist my body. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;. . . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Nothing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I lay slack in my seat, pinned by the claw piercing my gut. Sharp fingers trace my blood specked cheek, oddly warm. Her cybernetics pulsate the same extent as her eyes, as her grip loops around the claw . . . and cracks it. Falling apart . . . as she holds something over my torn flesh. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Briar . . . I’m here.” Her eyes are different . . so much is different . . . she definitely got taller . . . but that wide and worried smile . . . it's still the same. “I’m here for you little sis. I’ll get you out of here. I— I—”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I missed you Lily.” The worlds fall out of our lips with a tumblr of thirteen years of emotions, as somehow Lily and I lurch forward. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Falling out of the cockpit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The neural link rips . . . and I go slack. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Tumbling onto a patch of grass and wildflowers . . . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Lying on top of her, looking into her eyes. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Both of us panting . . . I’m definitely about to pass out . . . &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Lily's face . . . looks like mine, tech interweaves hers where mine holds scars, and pointed cat-like ears where mine are a hound’s. But the same nose. The same freckles. The same lips. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;{Thirteen years.}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She smells like blood, lemon, and apricots . . .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&amp;lt;The same lips&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;I kiss her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
